{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, Winter et al. (2023) compared their iconicity ratings to previously published judgments for a subset of the same words (Perlman et al., 2015), and obtained Pearson's correlation coefficients between 0.48 (for auditory stimuli) and 0.55 (for written stimuli).",
    "By comparison, the Pearson's correlation between GPT-4's ratings and the Winter et al. (2023) ratings was r = 0.63.",
    "GPT-4's ratings were also more correlated with the Perlman et al. (2015) ratings, for both auditory stimuli (r = 0.53, p <.001) and written stimuli (r = 0.58, p <.001).",
    "This is further evidence for the reliability of the GPT-4 ratings.",
    "(Additionally, data contamination from previously published datasets is unlikely to be the explanation here: see Supplementary Analysis 1 for more details.)"
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, Winter et al. (2023) compared their iconicity ratings to previously published judgments for a subset of the same words (Perlman et al., 2015), and obtained Pearson's correlation coefficients between 0.48 (for auditory stimuli) and 0.55 (for written stimuli).",
    "By comparison, the Pearson's correlation between GPT-4's ratings and the Winter et al. (2023) ratings was r = 0.63.",
